he correspondence between Franz Liszt and George Sand; Baudelaire's poetics; Richard Wagner's theory of the Gesamtkunstwerk, or total work of art; decadence and symbolism; and Heidegger's critique of the correspondence theory of truth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aSynesthesia in literature. 0aSynesthesiaxPhilosophy. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Aesthetics. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849363340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493633423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493633/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles